message.content: cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SI. The paper discusses a mechanism design framework for eliciting expertise from agents in a crowd-sourcing setting, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The framework also involves encouraging agents to invest effort and provide honest information, which relates to machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the concept of a hierarchy of information, which could be relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI).
